dding:72pt 72pt 72pt 72pt}.c16{font-size:7pt;font-family:"Times New Roman";font-weight:400}.c10{margin-left:35pt;text-indent:-35pt}.c13{height:0pt}.c15{height:11pt}.c12{text-indent:-8pt}.c18{font-style:italic}.c20{height:53pt}.title{padding-top:0pt;color:#000000;font-size:26pt;padding-bottom:3pt;font-family:"Arial";line-height:1.15;page-break-after:avoid;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left}.subtitle{padding-top:0pt;color:#666666;font-size:15pt;padding-bottom:16pt;font-family:"Arial";line-height:1.15;page-break-after:avoid;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left}li{color:#000000;font-size:11pt;font-family:"Arial"}p{margin:0;color:#000000;font-size:11pt;font-family:"Arial"}h1{padding-top:20pt;color:#000000;font-size:20pt;padding-bottom:6pt;font-family:"Arial";line-height:1.15;page-break-after:avoid;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left}h2{padding-top:18pt;color:#000000;font-size:16pt;padding-bottom:6pt;font-family:"Arial";line-height:1.15;page-break-after:avoid;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left}h3{padding-top:16pt;color:#434343;font-size:14pt;padding-bottom:4pt;font-family:"Arial";line-height:1.15;page-break-after:avoid;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left}h4{padding-top:14pt;color:#666666;font-size:12pt;padding-bottom:4pt;font-family:"Arial";line-height:1.15;page-break-after:avoid;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left}h5{padding-top:12pt;color:#666666;font-size:11pt;padding-bottom:4pt;font-family:"Arial";line-height:1.15;page-break-after:avoid;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left}h6{padding-top:12pt;color:#666666;font-size:11pt;padding-bottom:4pt;font-family:"Arial";line-height:1.15;page-break-after:avoid;font-style:italic;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left}</style></head><body class="c24"><p class="c2">

<span class="c0">THIS AGREEMENT</span>
<span class="c1">&nbsp;is dated</span></p>
<p class="c2"><span class="c3 c0">PARTIES</span></p>
<p class="c2"><span class="c0">(1) &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;CreatorSync </span>
<span class="c7">(</span><span class="c0">the Supplier</span><span class="c1">)</span></p
><p class="c2"><span class="c0">(2) &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  {{ Auth::user()->full_name }}</span></p><p class="c2">
<span class="c7">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;(</span>
<span class="c0">the Customer</span><span class="c1">)</span></p><p class="c2">

<span class="c0">BACKGROUND</span></p><p class="c2">
<span class="c1">The Company is a business engaged in assisting Dailymotion channels held by customers to grow through advertising opportunities. In order for the Customer to take advantage of advertising revenue opportunities the Customer wishes to engage the Company to manage advertising opportunities for the Customer on the terms of this Agreement.</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c0">AGREED TERMS</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c0">1.</span><span class="c7">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><span class="c3 c0">INTERPRETATION</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c1">The following definitions and rules of interpretation apply in this Agreement:</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c7">1.1.</span><span class="c16">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; </span>
<span class="c3 c0">Definitions</span></p><p class="c8">
<span class="c0">Agreement: </span>
<span class="c1">the agreement of the Customer to engage the Supplier to provide the Services on the terms and conditions set out hereafter</span></p><p class="c8"><span class="c0">Agreement Date: </span><span class="c1">the date this Agreement is dated.</span></p><p class="c8"><span class="c0">Business Day: </span><span class="c1">a day other than a Saturday, Sunday or public holiday in England when banks in London are open for business.</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c0">Day: </span><span class="c1">a period of 24 consecutive hours ending at 12.00 midnight</span></p><p class="c8"><span class="c0">Channel: </span><span class="c7">means</span><span class="c0">&nbsp;</span><span class="c1">each home page for an account held by the Customer on &nbsp;Daily Motion;</span></p><p class="c8"><span class="c0">Commencement Date: </span><span class="c1">the date from which the Supplier will provide the selected service.</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c0">Fixed Term:</span><span class="c1">&nbsp;the agreed period of the Selected Service as set out in Schedule 1 being a fixed term of years and/or months beginning on the Commencement Date</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c0">Impression: </span><span class="c1">Each complete run of an advertisement on a video.</span></p><p class="c8"><span class="c0">month:</span><span class="c1">&nbsp;a calendar month.</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c0">Nominated Channel:</span><span class="c1">&nbsp;Each Channel nominated by the Customer to receive the Selected Service pursuant to this agreement as set out in Schedule 2 and any further Channel owned by the Customer which the supplier may agree to include in the CreatorSync Network during the Term.</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c0">Official Video View: </span><span class="c1">means an authenticated view by an individual that is not software based or otherwise fake</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c0">CreatorSync Network: </span><span class="c1">means the Supplier&rsquo;s network of video content sites</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c0">Revenue Received: </span><span class="c1">Is the net amount of advertising revenue received by the Supplier pursuant to this Agreement after deduction of Dailymotion&rsquo;s &nbsp;charges.</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c0">Selected Service:</span><span class="c1">&nbsp;The Service selected by the Customer whether Standard, Pro or Elite as set out in Schedule 1</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c0">Services: </span><span class="c1">The services to be provided by the Supplier under this Agreement including targeted advertisements next to original video content, product placement and brand recognition within video content in accordance with the Selected Service</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c0">Sign up Bonus:</span><span class="c1">&nbsp;A payment made by the Supplier to the Customer as an incentive to select the Elite service</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c0">Termination Notice:</span><span class="c1">&nbsp;Notice in the form set out in Schedule 3.</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c0">View:</span><span class="c1">&nbsp;a view by an individual of video content on a Channel</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c0">Dailymotion</span><span class="c7">&nbsp;</span><span class="c0">:</span><span class="c1">&nbsp;the video sharing web-site</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c1">1.2. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clause, schedule and paragraph headings shall not affect the interpretation of this Agreement.</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c1">1.3. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;A person includes a natural person, corporate or unincorporated body (whether or not having a separate legal personality).</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c1">1.4. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Schedules form part of this Agreement and shall have effect as if set out in full in the body of this Agreement. &nbsp;Any reference to this Agreement includes the Schedules.</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c1">1.5. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Unless the context otherwise requires, words in the singular shall include the plural and in the plural shall include the singular.</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c1">1.6. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Unless the context otherwise requires, reference to one gender shall include a reference to the other genders.</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c1">1.7. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;A reference to a statute or statutory provision is a reference to it as it is enforced at the date of this Agreement.</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c1">1.8. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Reference to writing or written includes fax and email.</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c1">1.9. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Any obligation on a party not to do something includes an obligation not to allow that thing to be done. </span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c1">1.10.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;References to clauses and Schedules are to the clauses and Schedules of this Agreement.</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c1">1.11.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Any words following the terms including, include, in particular, for example or any similar expression shall be construed as illustrative and shall not limit the sense of the words, description, definition, phrase or term preceding those terms.</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c1">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c0">2. &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;COMMENCEMENT AND DURATION</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c1">2.1. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The Supplier shall provide the Services to the Customer from the Commencement Date</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c1">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c1">2.2. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The Services supplied in accordance with this Agreement shall continue to be supplied unless terminated in accordance with clause 2.3 or 2.4 of this Agreement or terminated in accordance with clause 10.1.</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c1">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c1">2.3 &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Where the Selected Service is the Standard Service the Customer may by notice to the supplier terminate this agreement with immediate effect at any time after the Commencement Date and if terminated in accordance with this clause the Supplier shall use its reasonable endeavours to ensure that the Customer&rsquo;s Nominated Channels are released by the Supplier from the CreatorSync &nbsp;within 30 days.</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c1">&nbsp;2.4 &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Where the Selected Service is Pro or Elite the Services supplied in accordance with this agreement shall continue initially for the Fixed Term and then automatically continue for a further period of 12 months and then annually thereafter unless or until the Agreement is terminated by either party in accordance with clause 2.5 below or clause 10.1.</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c1">&nbsp;2.5 &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Where the Selected Service is Pro or Elite this Agreement may be terminated by the Customer giving a Termination Notice to the Supplier of not less than 6 months prior to the last day of the Fixed Term or any continuation period in accordance with clause 2.4 above.</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c1">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c3 c0">3. &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;SUPPLIERS OBLIGATIONS</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c1">&nbsp;3.1 &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The Supplier shall move the Customers Nominated Channels into the CreatorSync Network Account</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c1">3.2 &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The Supplier shall provide the Customer with access to the Supplier&rsquo;s support services including guidance with technical issues</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c1">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c3 c0">4. &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;CUSTOMER&rsquo;S OBLIGATIONS</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c1">&nbsp;4.1. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The Customer agrees to:</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c1">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c1">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;(a) &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;co-operate with the Supplier in all matters relating to the provision of the Services;</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c1">(b) &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;provide, for the Supplier in a timely manner and at no charge to the Supplier, access to the Customer&rsquo;s data in respect of each Nominated Channel under this Agreement;</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c1">(c) &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;co-operate with the Supplier in moving the Customer&rsquo;s Nominated Channel into the CreatorSync</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c1">(d) &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;provide, in a timely manner, true and accurate information as to the history of the Customer&rsquo; Nominated Channels and relationship with Dailymotion or other similar video sharing web-sites;</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c1">(e) &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;be responsible (at the Customer&rsquo;s own cost) for maintaining the Nominated Channels during the Term including identifying and removing any virus or malware attached to a Nominated Channel or any video content on the Nominated Channel);</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c1">(f) &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;generate regular video content for the Nominated Channels and promote the Nominated Channels through social media</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c1">(g) &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;obtain and maintain all necessary licences and consents and comply with all relevant legislation in relation to each Nominated Channel before the date on which the Services are to start.</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c1">(h) &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;pay the charges for the Selected Services as set out in clause 5 and Schedule 1</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c1">&nbsp;4.2. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;If the Supplier&rsquo;s performance of its obligations under this Agreement is prevented or delayed by any act or omission of the Customer, its agents, subcontractors, consultants or employees, the Supplier shall not be liable for any costs, charges or losses sustained or incurred by the Customer that arise directly or indirectly from such prevention or delay.</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c1">&nbsp;4.3. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The Customer shall be liable to pay to the Supplier on demand, all reasonable costs, charges or losses sustained or incurred by the Supplier including any direct, indirect or consequential losses, loss of profit and loss of reputation and the loss or damage to property that arise directly or indirectly from the Customer&rsquo;s fraud, negligence, failure to perform or delay in the performance of any of its obligations under this Agreement, subject to the Supplier confirming such costs, charges and losses to the Customer in writing.</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c1">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c3 c0">5. &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;PAYMENT</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c0">&nbsp;</span><span class="c1">5.1. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;In consideration of the provision of the Services by the Supplier, the Supplier shall be entitled to retain a percentage of the Revenue Received.</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c1">&nbsp;5.2. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The percentage of the Revenue Received to be retained by the Customer from targeted advertising next to original video content on the Customer&rsquo;s Nominated Channels to shall be the agreed percentage retention as set out in Schedule 1</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c7 c18">5.3. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><span class="c1">The percentage of the Revenue Received to be retained by the Customer from the syndication of video content in accordance with clause 7.1.3 shall be the agreed percentage retention as set out in Schedule 1</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c7 c18">&nbsp;</span><span class="c1">5.4 &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The percentage of the Revenue Received to be retained by the Customer from product placement or brand integration in accordance with clause 7.1.3 shall be the agreed percentage retention as set out in Schedule 1</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c1">&nbsp;5.6 &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The Supplier shall provide the Customer with access to the Official Video View and revenue data for the Nominated Channels which shall be unfiltered and direct to the Customer from Daily Motion or other similar network if requested.</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c1">&nbsp;5.7 &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The Customer shall receive payment of the revenue received by the Supplier less the percentage retentions as set out in this clause 5 within 15 days following the last day of the calendar month in which the revenue is received by the Supplier.</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c1">&nbsp;5.7 &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The Customer shall not be entitled to receive payment from the Supplier for any revenue generated through the use of copyrighted material where the copyright in the material is owned by a third party; through the use of closed Channels or any Channels where monetization has been disabled; or through fake or otherwise unauthorised views and or followers.</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c1">&nbsp;5.8 &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The Supplier shall be entitled to withhold payment to the Customer if it is established to the reasonable satisfaction of the Supplier that the Customer has supplied information to the Supplier which is false in a material particular including but not limited to false personal details, or exaggerated claims for the popularity of a Nominated Channel</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c1">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="c2 c15"><span class="c1"></span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c3 c0">6. &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY RIGHTS</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c1">As between the Customer and the Supplier, all intellectual property rights in the delivery of the Services shall be owned by the Supplier.</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c1">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c3 c0">7. &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;BUSINESS AND CO-OPERATION</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c0">&nbsp;</span><span class="c1">7.1 &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;In consideration of the provision of the Services by the Supplier the Customer grants to the Supplier;</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c1">7.1.1 &nbsp; &nbsp;the exclusive right to sell and manage any and all of the customers&rsquo; existing advertising inventory on the Nominated Channels during the Term;</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c1">7.1.2 &nbsp; &nbsp;the exclusive right to sell and manage product placement and or brand integration opportunities for the video content uploaded to the Customer&rsquo;s Nominated Channels during the Term subject to the Customer&rsquo;s written approval of the brand</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c1">7.1.3 &nbsp;the exclusive right to license video content uploaded to the Customer&rsquo;s Nominated Channels for syndication in any manner across any platform, format, or communications medium</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c1">7.2 &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;In consideration of the provision of the Services by the Supplier the Customer and in order to promote the CreatorSync to a worldwide audience the Customer grants to the Supplier;</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c1">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;7.2.1 &nbsp; &nbsp;a non-exclusive, transferrable, worldwide, royalty free licence to use the Customer&rsquo;s name, image and/or likeness in connection with the promotion of the CreatorSync, channels on CreatorSync including the Nominated Channels.</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c1">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;7.2.2&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;a non-exclusive, transferrable worldwide, royalty free licence to display your trademarks and logos in connection with the promotion of CreatorSync, channels on CreatorSync including your Nominated Channels.</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c1">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="c2 c15"><span class="c3 c0"></span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c3 c0">8. &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;LIMITATION OF LIABILITY</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c1">&nbsp;8.1. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Nothing in this Agreement limits or excludes the Supplier&rsquo;s liability for:</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c1">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;8.1.1&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;death or personal injury caused by its negligence;</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c1">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;8.1.2&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;fraud or fraudulent misrepresentations; and</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c1">8.1.3&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;breach of the terms implied by Section 2 of the Supply of Goods and Services Act 1982 (title and acquired possession) or any other liability which cannot be limited or excluded by applicable law.</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c1">&nbsp;8.2. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Subject to clause 8.1, the Supplier shall not be liable to the Customer, whether in contract, tort (including negligence), for breach of statutory duty, or otherwise, arising under or in connection with this Agreement for:</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c1">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;8.2.1. &nbsp; loss of profits;</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c1">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;8.2.2. &nbsp; loss of sales or business;</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c1">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;8.2.3. &nbsp; loss of agreements or contracts;</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c1">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;8.2.4. &nbsp; loss of anticipated savings;</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c1">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;8.2.5. &nbsp; loss of or damage to goodwill;</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c1">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;8.2.6. &nbsp; loss of use or corruption of software, data or information;</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c1">&nb